{
  "stem": "7598.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I'm not talking about the Gestapo and the SS, but like this man who gave us a 48-hour transit.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We then went back, caught another train, crossed, spent two days on the train in Spain just to get off at stations and buy a bit of food, collected some lice on the way, and we eventually got to Portugal at the very beginning of May, 1942.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "When we arrived in Lisbon, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we went to the Belgian consulate.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we very gingerly sort of said downstairs at the reception that we were Lucien and Odette Rubinstein and we believe there's a visa waiting for us.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "At that point, a very nice young man came downstairs and put his arms on me, says, ah, he said, the Rubinstein children.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I've been waiting for them for months.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they made us very welcome and offered us food and found a hotel for us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "My parents were very fortunate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They were allowed to send out 50 pounds, I think a month, or 50 pounds once or twice to Portugal, because they knew there might be a wait for us before we'd be able to get some sort of transport from Portugal.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we got to this lovely little hotel.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We knew we were near the end of our ordeal.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we also--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, no, no.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Nice.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When we left Nice--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were on our own.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] And in Perpignan when we went to the consul, there's another little anecdote which I think is-- is quite important.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When we were at Perpignan my brother and I on our own went and had a cup of coffee.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
